lead_paragraph: An article last Sunday about Delaware’s status as a football swing state, with fans of both the Philadelphia Eagles and the Baltimore Ravens but with no N.F.L. team of its own, misstated the distance between the state’s northern and southern borders. It is 96 miles, not 76.
